{
  "texts": [
    "This also highlighted the importance of including EEG data in addition to the commonly used modalities in LLMs, such as audio and video.",
    "It should be noted that the cases with all modalities removed (the first line) used majority voting similar to Xuhai et al. 's setting [44], serving as the baseline for model performance.",
    "Performance of MultiEEG-GPT.",
    "TableFor the few-shot prompting, we observed a similar trend, with multimodal models outperforming single-modality models.",
    "Additionally, the 1-shot prompting achieved higher performance than zero-shot prompting, with relative improvements of 5.45%, 8.43%, 6.60% over zero-shot prompting for the MODMA, PME4 and LUMED-2 databases, respectively."
  ]
}